---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="etcd Leader Election" 
  description="Interactive visualization of etcd leader election — leases, campaigns, watches, and distributed locks"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" }, 
    { label: "etcd", href: "/etcd/" },
    { label: "Leader Election", href: "/etcd/leader-election/" }
  ]}
>
  <div class="viz-container">
    <header class="viz-header">
      <h1>🗳️ etcd Leader Election</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Leases, Campaigns, Watches &amp; Distributed Locks — Visualized</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section class="overview-section">
      <div class="overview-card">
        <p>
          <a href="https://etcd.io" target="_blank">etcd</a> is a distributed key-value store that
          uses <a href="/raft/">Raft consensus</a> under the hood. It powers
          <strong>Kubernetes</strong> (storing all cluster state), CoreDNS, and many distributed
          systems. etcd provides <em>linearizable</em> reads and writes, a <em>Watch API</em> for
          real-time notifications, and <strong>lease-based primitives</strong> for building leader
          election, distributed locks, and service discovery.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- etcd Cluster Visualization -->
    <section class="cluster-section">
      <h2>🖧 etcd Cluster</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">A 3-node etcd cluster with key-value store. The cluster uses Raft internally for consensus.</p>

      <div class="cluster-visual">
        <svg id="clusterSvg" viewBox="0 0 600 200" class="cluster-svg">
          <defs>
            <filter id="glow">
              <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="3" result="blur"/>
              <feMerge><feMergeNode in="blur"/><feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/></feMerge>
            </filter>
          </defs>
          <!-- Rendered by JS -->
          <g id="clusterNodes"></g>
          <g id="clusterMessages"></g>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <div class="kv-store" id="kvStore">
        <div class="kv-header">
          <span class="kv-title">📦 Key-Value Store</span>
          <span class="kv-revision" id="kvRevision">Revision: 1</span>
        </div>
        <div class="kv-entries" id="kvEntries">
          <div class="kv-empty">Store is empty</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Lease-Based Leader Election -->
    <section class="election-section">
      <h2>👑 Lease-Based Leader Election</h2>
      <div class="explain-card highlight-card">
        <h3>💡 How It Works</h3>
        <p>
          A <strong>lease</strong> is a time-to-live (TTL) contract with the etcd cluster. To become
          leader, a candidate creates a lease (e.g., 15s TTL), then tries to write a key like
          <code>/election/leader</code> with the lease attached. The <em>first writer wins</em> via
          atomic compare-and-create (revision = 0 means "key must not exist"). The leader must
          keep the lease alive by sending <strong>KeepAlive</strong> requests every TTL/3. If the
          leader crashes, the lease expires, the key is deleted, and a new election begins.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="election-controls">
        <button id="startElectionBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🏁 Start Election Demo</button>
        <button id="stepElectionBtn" class="action-btn step-btn" disabled>⏭️ Next Step</button>
        <button id="resetElectionBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
      </div>

      <div class="election-status" id="electionStatus">
        <span class="status-badge idle">Ready</span>
        <span class="status-text" id="electionStatusText">Click "Start Election Demo" to begin</span>
      </div>

      <div class="candidates-grid" id="candidatesGrid">
        <div class="candidate-card" data-id="0">
          <div class="candidate-header">
            <span class="candidate-icon">🖥️</span>
            <span class="candidate-name">Node A</span>
            <span class="candidate-role" id="candidateRole0">Follower</span>
          </div>
          <div class="lease-bar-container">
            <div class="lease-bar" id="leaseBar0"></div>
            <span class="lease-label" id="leaseLabel0">No lease</span>
          </div>
          <div class="candidate-status" id="candidateStatus0">Idle</div>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-card" data-id="1">
          <div class="candidate-header">
            <span class="candidate-icon">🖥️</span>
            <span class="candidate-name">Node B</span>
            <span class="candidate-role" id="candidateRole1">Follower</span>
          </div>
          <div class="lease-bar-container">
            <div class="lease-bar" id="leaseBar1"></div>
            <span class="lease-label" id="leaseLabel1">No lease</span>
          </div>
          <div class="candidate-status" id="candidateStatus1">Idle</div>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-card" data-id="2">
          <div class="candidate-header">
            <span class="candidate-icon">🖥️</span>
            <span class="candidate-name">Node C</span>
            <span class="candidate-role" id="candidateRole2">Follower</span>
          </div>
          <div class="lease-bar-container">
            <div class="lease-bar" id="leaseBar2"></div>
            <span class="lease-label" id="leaseLabel2">No lease</span>
          </div>
          <div class="candidate-status" id="candidateStatus2">Idle</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Election Campaign Flow -->
    <section class="campaign-section">
      <h2>🏛️ Election Campaign Flow</h2>
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>📋 Campaign, Resign &amp; Proclaim</h3>
        <p>
          The <strong>Campaign</strong> operation creates a lease and attempts to create an election
          key. If the key already exists (another leader), the candidate <em>watches</em> and waits.
          <strong>Resign</strong> deletes the key, triggering a new election. <strong>Proclaim</strong>
          lets the leader update its value (announce a new configuration, for example).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="campaign-controls">
        <div class="campaign-node" data-node="0">
          <span class="campaign-node-label">Node A</span>
          <button class="action-btn campaign-btn" data-action="campaign" data-node="0">📢 Campaign</button>
          <button class="action-btn resign-btn" data-action="resign" data-node="0" disabled>🏳️ Resign</button>
          <button class="action-btn proclaim-btn" data-action="proclaim" data-node="0" disabled>📣 Proclaim</button>
        </div>
        <div class="campaign-node" data-node="1">
          <span class="campaign-node-label">Node B</span>
          <button class="action-btn campaign-btn" data-action="campaign" data-node="1">📢 Campaign</button>
          <button class="action-btn resign-btn" data-action="resign" data-node="1" disabled>🏳️ Resign</button>
          <button class="action-btn proclaim-btn" data-action="proclaim" data-node="1" disabled>📣 Proclaim</button>
        </div>
        <div class="campaign-node" data-node="2">
          <span class="campaign-node-label">Node C</span>
          <button class="action-btn campaign-btn" data-action="campaign" data-node="2">📢 Campaign</button>
          <button class="action-btn resign-btn" data-action="resign" data-node="2" disabled>🏳️ Resign</button>
          <button class="action-btn proclaim-btn" data-action="proclaim" data-node="2" disabled>📣 Proclaim</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="campaign-visual" id="campaignVisual">
        <div class="campaign-election-key">
          <span class="ek-label">🔑 /election/leader</span>
          <span class="ek-value" id="ekValue">&#x2205; empty</span>
          <span class="ek-revision" id="ekRevision">rev: 0</span>
        </div>
        <div class="campaign-waiters" id="campaignWaiters">
          <!-- Waiters shown here -->
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="campaign-status" id="campaignStatus">
        <span class="status-badge idle">Ready</span>
        <span class="status-text" id="campaignStatusText">Click Campaign on any node to begin</span>
      </div>

      <button id="killLeaderBtn" class="action-btn chaos-btn" disabled>💀 Kill Leader</button>
    </section>

    <!-- Watch-Based Coordination -->
    <section class="watch-section">
      <h2>👁️ Watch-Based Coordination</h2>
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>📡 Real-Time Notifications</h3>
        <p>
          Watchers subscribe to key prefixes and receive notifications whenever keys are created,
          updated, or deleted. Each event includes the <strong>revision</strong> number. Watches
          start from a specific revision, so clients never miss events. etcd compacts old revisions
          to reclaim space — watchers that fall too far behind get a "compacted" error.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="watch-demo">
        <div class="watch-controls">
          <div class="watch-input-group">
            <input type="text" id="watchKeyInput" class="watch-input" placeholder="Key (e.g., /config/db)" value="/config/db">
            <input type="text" id="watchValueInput" class="watch-input" placeholder="Value" value="host=10.0.0.1">
            <button id="watchPutBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">📝 Put</button>
            <button id="watchDeleteBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🗑️ Delete</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="watch-panels">
          <div class="watch-panel">
            <div class="watch-panel-header">
              <span>👁️ Watcher 1</span>
              <span class="watch-prefix">/config/*</span>
            </div>
            <div class="watch-events" id="watchEvents1"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="watch-panel">
            <div class="watch-panel-header">
              <span>👁️ Watcher 2</span>
              <span class="watch-prefix">/config/*</span>
            </div>
            <div class="watch-events" id="watchEvents2"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="watch-panel">
            <div class="watch-panel-header">
              <span>👁️ Watcher 3</span>
              <span class="watch-prefix">/config/*</span>
            </div>
            <div class="watch-events" id="watchEvents3"></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="watch-info">
          <div class="info-chip">
            <span class="info-label">Watch Revision</span>
            <span class="info-value" id="watchRevision">1</span>
          </div>
          <div class="info-chip">
            <span class="info-label">Compact Revision</span>
            <span class="info-value" id="compactRevision">0</span>
          </div>
          <button id="compactBtn" class="action-btn step-btn">🗜️ Compact</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Distributed Locks -->
    <section class="lock-section">
      <h2>🔒 Distributed Locks</h2>
      <div class="explain-card highlight-card">
        <h3>🔑 Fair Lock Queue (No Thundering Herd)</h3>
        <p>
          etcd implements distributed locks using a <em>prefix + revision ordering</em> pattern.
          Each process creates a unique key under <code>/locks/mylock/</code> with a lease. The
          process whose key has the <strong>smallest revision</strong> holds the lock. Others
          don't poll — they <em>watch the key just before theirs</em> in revision order. When that
          key is deleted, the next process gets the lock. This avoids the
          <strong>thundering herd</strong> problem — only one waiter wakes up at a time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="lock-controls">
        <button id="lockAcquireBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🔒 Acquire Lock (3 processes)</button>
        <button id="lockReleaseBtn" class="action-btn step-btn" disabled>🔓 Release Lock (holder)</button>
        <button id="lockResetBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
      </div>

      <div class="lock-visual">
        <div class="lock-key-header">
          <span>🔑 /locks/mylock/</span>
        </div>
        <div class="lock-queue" id="lockQueue">
          <div class="lock-empty">No lock contention — click Acquire to start</div>
        </div>
        <div class="lock-watch-arrows" id="lockWatchArrows"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="lock-status" id="lockStatus">
        <span class="status-badge idle">Ready</span>
        <span class="status-text" id="lockStatusText">Click "Acquire Lock" to see the queue mechanism</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Event Log -->
    <section class="event-log-section">
      <h2>📋 Event Log</h2>
      <div class="event-log" id="eventLog">
        <div class="event-log-empty">Events will appear here...</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="viz-footer">
      <p>Based on <a href="https://etcd.io/docs/v3.5/dev-guide/interacting_v3/" target="_blank">etcd v3 documentation</a> and <a href="https://pkg.go.dev/go.etcd.io/etcd/client/v3/concurrency" target="_blank">etcd concurrency package</a></p>
    </footer>

    <div class="share-buttons">
      <span>Share this visualization:</span>
      <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Interactive%20etcd%20leader%20election%20visualization&url=https://systeminternals.dev/etcd/leader-election/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">𝕏 Twitter</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://systeminternals.dev/etcd/leader-election/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">in LinkedIn</a>
      <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/submitlink?u=https://systeminternals.dev/etcd/leader-election/&t=Interactive%20etcd%20Leader%20Election%20Visualizer" target="_blank" class="share-btn">🟧 Hacker News</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .viz-container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .viz-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .viz-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f59e0b, #ef4444, #8b5cf6);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .section-desc {
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* Overview */
  .overview-section { margin-bottom: 50px; }
  .overview-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1), rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.05));
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #ccc;
  }
  .overview-card strong { color: #fff; }
  .overview-card em { color: #f59e0b; font-style: normal; font-weight: 500; }
  .overview-card a { color: #60a5fa; }

  /* Action Buttons */
  .action-btn {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .action-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.4; cursor: not-allowed; }
  .primary-btn { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f59e0b, #d97706); color: white; }
  .primary-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.4); }
  .step-btn { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #60a5fa, #3b82f6); color: white; }
  .step-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4); }
  .reset-btn { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: #ccc; }
  .reset-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); }
  .chaos-btn { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ef4444, #dc2626); color: white; }
  .chaos-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.4); }
  .campaign-btn { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4ade80, #22c55e); color: white; font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 6px 12px; }
  .campaign-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .resign-btn { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fb923c, #f97316); color: white; font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 6px 12px; }
  .resign-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .proclaim-btn { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a78bfa, #7c3aed); color: white; font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 6px 12px; }
  .proclaim-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { transform: translateY(-1px); }

  /* Status */
  .election-status, .campaign-status, .lock-status {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .status-badge {
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .status-badge.idle { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: #999; }
  .status-badge.active { background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.2); color: #f59e0b; }
  .status-badge.success { background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.2); color: #4ade80; }
  .status-badge.error { background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2); color: #ef4444; }
  .status-text { color: #aaa; font-size: 0.9rem; }

  /* Cluster SVG */
  .cluster-section { margin-bottom: 50px; }
  .cluster-visual { margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .cluster-svg { width: 100%; height: auto; }

  /* KV Store */
  .kv-store {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }
  .kv-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  }
  .kv-title { font-weight: 600; color: #fff; }
  .kv-revision { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #888; font-family: monospace; }
  .kv-entries { padding: 12px 16px; min-height: 40px; }
  .kv-empty { color: #555; font-style: italic; }
  .kv-entry {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 6px 10px;
    margin: 4px 0;
    background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }
  .kv-entry.new { animation: kvFlash 0.6s ease; }
  @keyframes kvFlash {
    0% { background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.4); }
    100% { background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.08); }
  }
  .kv-key { color: #f59e0b; }
  .kv-val { color: #ccc; }
  .kv-lease { color: #8b5cf6; font-size: 0.75rem; }

  /* Election Section */
  .election-section { margin-bottom: 50px; }
  .election-controls { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 16px; }

  /* Candidates Grid */
  .candidates-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }
  .candidate-card {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }
  .candidate-card.leader {
    border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.5);
    background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.05);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1);
  }
  .candidate-card.waiting {
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
  }
  .candidate-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .candidate-icon { font-size: 1.2rem; }
  .candidate-name { font-weight: 600; color: #fff; }
  .candidate-role {
    margin-left: auto;
    padding: 2px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    color: #999;
  }
  .candidate-role.leader-role { background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.2); color: #f59e0b; }
  .candidate-role.waiting-role { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2); color: #60a5fa; }

  .lease-bar-container {
    position: relative;
    height: 20px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .lease-bar {
    height: 100%;
    width: 0%;
    border-radius: 10px;
    transition: width 0.3s linear;
  }
  .lease-bar.active { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #4ade80, #22c55e); }
  .lease-bar.expiring { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f59e0b, #ef4444); }
  .lease-bar.expired { background: #ef4444; width: 0% !important; }
  .lease-label {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #fff;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
  }
  .candidate-status { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #888; }

  /* Campaign Section */
  .campaign-section { margin-bottom: 50px; }
  .campaign-controls {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .campaign-node {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 10px;
  }
  .campaign-node-label { font-weight: 600; color: #fff; min-width: 55px; }

  .campaign-visual {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .campaign-election-key {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.25);
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-family: monospace;
  }
  .ek-label { color: #f59e0b; font-weight: 600; }
  .ek-value { color: #ccc; }
  .ek-revision { margin-left: auto; color: #888; font-size: 0.85rem; }

  .campaign-waiters {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .waiter-chip {
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    animation: fadeIn 0.3s ease;
  }
  .waiter-chip.watching { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.15); color: #60a5fa; border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3); }
  @keyframes fadeIn { from { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0.9); } to { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); } }

  /* Watch Section */
  .watch-section { margin-bottom: 50px; }
  .watch-demo { margin-top: 20px; }
  .watch-controls { margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .watch-input-group { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; }
  .watch-input {
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    width: 200px;
  }
  .watch-input::placeholder { color: #555; }

  .watch-panels {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .watch-panel {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
